#: ../../N/net-police.rst:9
msgid ""
"(var. : net.cops) Those Usenet readers who feel it is their responsibility "
"to pounce on and :ref:`flame` any posting which they regard as offensive or "
"in violation of their understanding of :ref:`netiquette`\\. Generally used "
"sarcastically or pejoratively. Also spelled ‘net police’. See also "
":ref:`net--`\\, :ref:`code-police`\\."
msgstr ""
"(別表記: net.cops) 不快だと、あるいは自分たちの理解する\\ :ref:`netiquette`\\ "
"に違反していると見なす投稿に飛びかかって\\ :ref:`flame`\\ "
"することが自分の責任だと感じるUsenet読者たち。一般に皮肉的または蔑称的に使われる。‘net police’とも綴られる。\\ "
":ref:`net--`\\ 、\\ :ref:`code-police`\\ も参照。"
